ontologyFramework.OFDataMapping.complexDataType

Class ExceptionDataMapper

  • java.lang.Object
    • ontologyFramework.OFDataMapping.complexDataType.ExceptionDataMapper
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, OFDataMapperInterface<org.semanticweb.owlapi.model.OWLNamedIndividual,java.lang.String>

    public class ExceptionDataMapper
extends java.lang.Object
implements OFDataMapperInterface<org.semanticweb.owlapi.model.OWLNamedIndividual,java.lang.String>
    This class implements a mapping mechanism between an individual and a String to represent a particolar message carried out from an exception. This class is created and initialized using OFDataMapperBuilder; furthermore, it can be retrieved trougth the static map manager: OFBuildedListInvoker. A further possibility is to build a similar mapper between individual an an Exception Object, eventually defined into the system. Anyway, this has not been done since the behavior of the system when an error occurs could have very different nature. For this reason a particular building process (defined by OFExceptionBuilder) has been define for exceptions. In particular it returns a string pointed by the data property: hasTypeExceptionMessage; which is defined by the second key word assign to the individual: M_ExeptionMessageMapper. This implementation supposes that an individual can have only one property like it.

    1.0

      • replaceIntoOntology

        public boolean replaceIntoOntology(org.semanticweb.owlapi.model.OWLNamedIndividual arg,
                          java.lang.String oldArg,
                          java.lang.String newArg,
                          OWLReferences ontoRef)
        Description copied from interface: OFDataMapperInterface
        Replace the value of an ontological entity in atomic way. Which means that, given an ontological entity E with a particular property A. The method will assign to A the new value and will remove the old one with no possibilities for the reasoner to update the data structure during those operations. Note that E is given as input while A should be encoded in the implementation of the interface.
        Specified by:
        replaceIntoOntology in interface OFDataMapperInterface<org.semanticweb.owlapi.model.OWLNamedIndividual,java.lang.String>
        Parameters:
        arg - ontological entity for which replace the values
        oldArg - value to remove
        newArg - value to add
        ontoRef - OWL references to the ontology
        Returns:
        true if the operation is successfully completed
